<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-79-0585 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author considers that the Chernobyl accident has underlined the limitsof national legislation as an instrument for the regulation of the nuclearindustry. It illustrates the need for co-operation among states and thepotential of any nuclear accident for transborder damage. The aftermathof the accident has revealed the essential role of international organisationsin providing guidance for national rule-making (NEA).</TEXT></DOC>